{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845926811,"sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","part":{"id":"prt_d78aa676b00162hBu38Q6OQXg2","messageID":"msg_d78aa584d001xOJBVPN5b7rify","sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-967eb2ad9e7a4a1591992a303b5d353b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775845926794,"end":1775845926809}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775845926831,"sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","part":{"id":"prt_d78aa679b001AV3FVzAWrd21Bs","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d78aa584d001xOJBVPN5b7rify","sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":51663,"input":5046,"output":90,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":46527}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775845928159,"sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","part":{"id":"prt_d78aa6cdc001unk0Bxek24jggt","messageID":"msg_d78aa67c3001vZD9ej96f0mfZr","sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775846090638,"sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","part":{"id":"prt_d78ace6fb001h36CewbTJdvwwr","messageID":"msg_d78aa67c3001vZD9ej96f0mfZr","sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e75be1d8beed4231acd73b8711161bdf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-007 Design — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language**: Go  \n**Size**: L  \n**Purpose**: Implement Kubernetes-native reconciler controllers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs using controller-runtime, providing automated lifecycle management for sandbox resources with proper event handling and status reporting.\n\n## Overview\n\nThis AR implements a proper Kubernetes reconciler pattern using `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` to manage AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources. The reconcilers will watch for changes to these CRDs and automatically manage the lifecycle of associated sandbox resources, updating status conditions and ensuring the desired state is achieved.\n\n### Key Requirements\n\n- Watch AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs for create/update/delete events\n- Reconcile sandbox resources using the agent-sandbox API\n- Maintain accurate status conditions (Ready, Error, Progressing, etc.)\n- Handle spec changes gracefully (rolling updates, reconfiguration)\n- Implement proper event recording and finalizer handling\n- Provide metrics for reconciliation performance\n- Support leader election for high availability\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Package Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/controller/\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── agentruntime.go         # AgentRuntime reconciler implementation\n│   ├── codeinterpreter.go      # CodeInterpreter reconciler implementation\n│   ├── controller.go           # Controller setup and manager initialization\n│   ├── predicates.go           # Event filtering predicates\n│   ├── finalizers.go           # Finalizer management utilities\n│   ├── status.go               # Status condition management\n│   └── metrics.go              # Reconciler metrics\n├── controller.go               # Existing HTTP-based controller (unchanged)\n└── sandbox.go                  # Existing sandbox creation logic (refactored)\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Controller-Runtime Manager                   │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │              AgentRuntime Reconciler                     │   │\n│  │  - Watches AgentRuntime CRDs                             │   │\n│  │  - Reconciles on spec changes                            │   │\n│  │  - Manages Sandbox CR lifecycle                          │   │\n│  │  - Updates AgentRuntime.Status                           │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                  │\n│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │            CodeInterpreter Reconciler                     │   │\n│  │  - Watches CodeInterpreter CRDs                          │   │\n│  │  - Reconciles on spec changes                            │   │\n│  │  - Manages Sandbox CR lifecycle                          │   │\n│  │  - Updates CodeInterpreter.Status                        │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n          │                     │                     │\n          │                     │                     │\n          ▼                     ▼                     ▼\n┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│  Kubernetes API  │  │   agent-sandbox  │  │     Redis        │\n│  (client-go)     │  │      API         │  │  (session store) │\n│  - AgentRuntime  │  │  - Sandbox CR    │  │  - Metadata      │\n│  - CodeInterpreter│ │  - SandboxClaim  │  │  - Activity TTL  │\n│  - Status updates│  │                  │  │                  │\n└──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Reconciliation Flow\n\n```\nEvent Triggered (Create/Update/Delete)\n    ↓\n[Predicate Filter] Ignore if status-only update or deletion timestamp set\n    ↓\n[Reconcile Entrypoint] Load resource from cache\n    ↓\n[Finalizer Check] Add finalizer if not present (for cleanup)\n    ↓\n[Deletion Check] If deletion timestamp set:\n    - Delete associated sandbox resources\n    - Remove finalizer\n    - Return\n    ↓\n[Spec Validation] Validate spec fields\n    ↓\n[Desired State Calculation] Determine what needs to be created/updated\n    ↓\n[Sandbox Reconciliation] Create/update/delete Sandbox CR\n    ↓\n[Status Update] Update status conditions\n    ↓\n[Event Recording] Record Kubernetes events\n    ↓\n[Metrics Update] Update Prometheus metrics\n    ↓\n[Return] Result: Requeue or Done\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Reconciler Structs\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/agentruntime.go`\n\n```go\n// AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n\tclient.Client\n\tScheme     *runtime.Scheme\n\tRecorder   record.EventRecorder\n\tSandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n\tStore       store.Store\n\tConfig      *controller.Config\n\n\t// Reconciliation configuration\n\tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n\tMaxReconciles int\n}\n\n// AgentRuntimeReconcilerOptions provides options for configuring the reconciler\ntype AgentRuntimeReconcilerOptions struct {\n\tRateLimiter workqueue.RateLimiter\n}\n```\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/codeinterpreter.go`\n\n```go\n// CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\ntype CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n\tclient.Client\n\tScheme       *runtime.Scheme\n\tRecorder     record.EventRecorder\n\tSandboxClient agentv1.SandboxInterface\n\tStore        store.Store\n\tConfig       *controller.Config\n\n\t// Reconciliation configuration\n\tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n\tMaxReconciles int\n}\n```\n\n### Status Conditions\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/status.go`\n\n```go\n// Condition types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter\nconst (\n\t// ConditionTypeReady indicates the resource is ready to serve requests\n\tConditionTypeReady = \"Ready\"\n\t\n\t// ConditionTypeAvailable indicates the runtime is available\n\tConditionTypeAvailable = \"Available\"\n\t\n\t// ConditionTypeProgressing indicates the resource is being reconciled\n\tConditionTypeProgressing = \"Progressing\"\n\t\n\t// ConditionTypeError indicates an error occurred during reconciliation\n\tConditionTypeError = \"Error\"\n\t\n\t// ConditionTypeSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox resource was created\n\tConditionTypeSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n)\n\n// Reason constants\nconst (\n\t// Reconciliation reasons\n\tReasonReconciliationStarted = \"ReconciliationStarted\"\n\tReasonReconciliationComplete = \"ReconciliationComplete\"\n\tReasonReconciliationFailed = \"ReconciliationFailed\"\n\t\n\t// Sandbox creation reasons\n\tReasonSandboxCreating = \"SandboxCreating\"\n\tReasonSandboxCreated = \"SandboxCreated\"\n\tReasonSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdating = \"SandboxUpdating\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdated = \"SandboxUpdated\"\n\tReasonSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleting = \"SandboxDeleting\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleted = \"SandboxDeleted\"\n\tReasonSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n\t\n\t// Validation reasons\n\tReasonValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n\tReasonSpecInvalid = \"SpecInvalid\"\n\t\n\t// Cleanup reasons\n\tReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n)\n\n// SetCondition sets a condition on the resource status\nfunc SetCondition(status *metav1.ConditionManager, conditionType, reason, message string, status metav1.ConditionStatus, timestamp metav1.Time)\n\n// GetCondition gets a condition of the specified type\nfunc GetCondition(conditions []metav1.Condition, conditionType string) *metav1.Condition\n\n// IsReady returns true if the resource is ready\nfunc IsReady(conditions []metav1.Condition) bool\n```\n\n### Finalizers\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/finalizers.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t// FinalizerAgentRuntime is the finalizer for AgentRuntime resources\n\tFinalizerAgentRuntime = \"agentruntime.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n\t\n\t// FinalizerCodeInterpreter is the finalizer for CodeInterpreter resources\n\tFinalizerCodeInterpreter = \"codeinterpreter.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/finalizer\"\n)\n\n// AddFinalizer adds a finalizer to the resource if not already present\nfunc AddFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error\n\n// RemoveFinalizer removes a finalizer from the resource\nfunc RemoveFinalizer(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, obj client.Object, finalizer string) error\n\n// HasFinalizer checks if the resource has the specified finalizer\nfunc HasFinalizer(obj client.Object, finalizer string) bool\n```\n\n### Predicates\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/predicates.go`\n\n```go\n// ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate filters events based on generation changes\ntype ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// SetupWithManager registers the predicate with the controller\nfunc (p *ResourceGenerationChangedPredicate) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n\n// LabelChangedPredicate filters events based on label changes\ntype LabelChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// AnnotationChangedPredicate filters events based on annotation changes\ntype AnnotationChangedPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n\n// PauseAnnotationPredicate filters events for resources with pause annotation\ntype PauseAnnotationPredicate struct {\n\tpredicate.Funcs\n}\n```\n\n### Metrics\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/metrics.go`\n\n```go\nconst (\n\t// Reconciler metrics\n\tmetricReconcileTotal = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_total\"\n\tmetricReconcileErrors = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_errors_total\"\n\tmetricReconcileDuration = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_duration_seconds\"\n\tmetricReconcileRequeues = \"workloadmanager_reconcile_requeues_total\"\n\t\n\t// Resource metrics\n\tmetricResourcesReady = \"workloadmanager_resources_ready\"\n\tmetricResourcesPending = \"workloadmanager_resources_pending\"\n\tmetricResourcesError = \"workloadmanager_resources_error\"\n\t\n\t// Sandbox metrics\n\tmetricSandboxCreations = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_creations_total\"\n\tmetricSandboxDeletions = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_deletions_total\"\n\tmetricSandboxUpdateDuration = \"workloadmanager_sandbox_update_duration_seconds\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\treconcileTotal = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n\t\tprometheus.CounterOpts{\n\t\t\tName: metricReconcileTotal,\n\t\t\tHelp: \"Total number of reconciliation operations\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"namespace\", \"name\"},\n\t)\n\t\n\treconcileDuration = prometheus.NewHistogramVec(\n\t\tprometheus.HistogramOpts{\n\t\t\tName:    metricReconcileDuration,\n\t\t\tHelp:    \"Reconciliation duration in seconds\",\n\t\t\tBuckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n\t\t},\n\t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"result\"},\n\t)\n\t\n\tresourcesReady = prometheus.NewGaugeVec(\n\t\tprometheus.GaugeOpts{\n\t\t\tName: metricResourcesReady,\n\t\t\tHelp: \"Number of ready resources\",\n\t\t},\n\t\t[]string{\"controller\", \"namespace\"},\n\t)\n)\n\n// RecordReconciliation records a reconciliation operation\nfunc RecordReconciliation(controller, namespace, name string, duration float64, result string)\n\n// RecordSandboxOperation records a sandbox operation\nfunc RecordSandboxOperation(operation, namespace, name string, duration float64, err error)\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Reconciler Interfaces\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/controller.go`\n\n```go\n// Reconciler defines the interface for all reconcilers\ntype Reconciler interface {\n\tReconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n\tSetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error\n}\n\n// ControllerConfig provides configuration for reconcilers\ntype ControllerConfig struct {\n\t// RequeueAfter is the default requeue interval\n\tRequeueAfter time.Duration\n\t\n\t// MaxConcurrentReconciles is the maximum number of concurrent reconciles\n\tMaxConcurrentReconciles int\n\t\n\t// SyncPeriod is the full resync period\n\tSyncPeriod *time.Duration\n\t\n\t// EnableLeaderElection enables leader election\n\tEnableLeaderElection bool\n\t\n\t// LeaderElectionID is the leader election ID\n\tLeaderElectionID string\n\t\n\t// LeaderElectionNamespace is the namespace for leader election\n\tLeaderElectionNamespace string\n\t\n\t// MetricsAddr is the metrics server address\n\tMetricsAddr string\n\t\n\t// EnableProfiling enables profiling endpoints\n\tEnableProfiling bool\n\t\n\t// ProbeAddr is the health probe address\n\tProbeAddr string\n}\n\n// NewControllerManager creates a new controller manager\nfunc NewControllerManager(cfg *rest.Config, controllerCfg *ControllerConfig) (ctrl.Manager, error)\n\n// SetupWithManager sets up all controllers with the manager\nfunc SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, store store.Store, controllerCfg *ControllerConfig) error\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime Reconcile Method\n\n```go\n// Reconcile reconciles AgentRuntime resources\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\tlog.Info(\"Reconciling AgentRuntime\", \"namespace\", req.Namespace, \"name\", req.Name)\n\t\n\tstartTime := time.Now()\n\t\n\t// Fetch the AgentRuntime instance\n\tagentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n\tif err := r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n\t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime resource not found. Ignoring since object must be deleted\")\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get AgentRuntime\")\n\t\tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Check if resource is being deleted\n\tif !agentRuntime.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn r.reconcileDelete(ctx, agentRuntime)\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Add finalizer if not present\n\tif !HasFinalizer(agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime) {\n\t\tif err := AddFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to add finalizer\")\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Validate spec\n\tif err := r.validateSpec(agentRuntime); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Spec validation failed\")\n\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n\t\t\tReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Reconcile sandbox\n\tsandboxResult, err := r.reconcileSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to reconcile sandbox\")\n\t\tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Update status based on sandbox result\n\tif sandboxResult.Created {\n\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeSandboxCreated, \n\t\t\tReasonSandboxCreated, \"Sandbox resource created successfully\")\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Check if ready\n\tready := r.isReady(agentRuntime)\n\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeReady, \n\t\tReasonReconciliationComplete, \"AgentRuntime is ready\")\n\t\n\t// Record metrics\n\tduration := time.Since(startTime).Seconds()\n\tresult := \"success\"\n\tif !ready {\n\t\tresult = \"requeue\"\n\t}\n\tRecordReconciliation(\"agentruntime\", req.Namespace, req.Name, duration, result)\n\t\n\t// Requeue if not ready\n\tif !ready {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime not ready, requeuing\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tlog.Info(\"Reconciliation completed successfully\")\n\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n}\n```\n\n### CodeInterpreter Reconcile Method\n\n```go\n// Reconcile reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\nfunc (r *CodeInterpreterReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\tlog.Info(\"Reconciling CodeInterpreter\", \"namespace\", req.Namespace, \"name\", req.Name)\n\t\n\tstartTime := time.Now()\n\t\n\t// Fetch the CodeInterpreter instance\n\tcodeInterpreter := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{}\n\tif err := r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, codeInterpreter); err != nil {\n\t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\tlog.Info(\"CodeInterpreter resource not found. Ignoring since object must be deleted\")\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get CodeInterpreter\")\n\t\tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Check if resource is being deleted\n\tif !codeInterpreter.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn r.reconcileDelete(ctx, codeInterpreter)\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Add finalizer if not present\n\tif !HasFinalizer(codeInterpreter, FinalizerCodeInterpreter) {\n\t\tif err := AddFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, codeInterpreter, FinalizerCodeInterpreter); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to add finalizer\")\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Validate spec\n\tif err := r.validateSpec(codeInterpreter); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Spec validation failed\")\n\t\tr.Recorder.Event(codeInterpreter, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n\t\t\tReasonSpecInvalid, err.Error())\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Reconcile sandbox\n\tsandboxResult, err := r.reconcileSandbox(ctx, codeInterpreter)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to reconcile sandbox\")\n\t\tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), \"error\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Update status based on sandbox result\n\tif sandboxResult.Created {\n\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeSandboxCreated, \n\t\t\tReasonSandboxCreated, \"Sandbox resource created successfully\")\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Check if ready\n\tready := r.isReady(codeInterpreter)\n\tr.updateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.ConditionTrue, ConditionTypeReady, \n\t\tReasonReconciliationComplete, \"CodeInterpreter is ready\")\n\t\n\t// Record metrics\n\tduration := time.Since(startTime).Seconds()\n\tresult := \"success\"\n\tif !ready {\n\t\tresult = \"requeue\"\n\t}\n\tRecordReconciliation(\"codeinterpreter\", req.Namespace, req.Name, duration, result)\n\t\n\t// Requeue if not ready\n\tif !ready {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"CodeInterpreter not ready, requeuing\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tlog.Info(\"Reconciliation completed successfully\")\n\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Sandbox Reconciliation\n\n```go\n// reconcileSandbox creates or updates the sandbox resource\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcileSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\t\n\tsandboxName := getSandboxName(agentRuntime)\n\t\n\t// Check if sandbox already exists\n\texistingSandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n\texistingSandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n\t})\n\t\n\terr := r.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: agentRuntime.Namespace,\n\t\tName:      sandboxName,\n\t}, existingSandbox)\n\t\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t// Create new sandbox\n\t\t\treturn r.createSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime, sandboxName)\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get sandbox: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Update existing sandbox\n\treturn r.updateSandbox(ctx, agentRuntime, existingSandbox, sandboxName)\n}\n\n// createSandbox creates a new sandbox resource\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) createSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, sandboxName string) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\tlog.Info(\"Creating sandbox\", \"name\", sandboxName)\n\t\n\tstartTime := time.Now()\n\t\n\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n\t})\n\tsandbox.SetName(sandboxName)\n\tsandbox.SetNamespace(agentRuntime.Namespace)\n\t\n\t// Set labels\n\tlabels := map[string]string{\n\t\tconstants.LabelManagedBy:    constants.LabelManagedByValue,\n\t\tconstants.LabelWorkloadName: agentRuntime.Name,\n\t\tconstants.LabelKind:         \"AgentRuntime\",\n\t}\n\tsandbox.SetLabels(labels)\n\t\n\t// Build spec from AgentRuntime spec\n\tspec, err := r.buildSandboxSpec(agentRuntime)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox spec: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tsandbox.Object[\"spec\"] = spec\n\t\n\t// Create sandbox\n\tif err := r.Create(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to create sandbox\")\n\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxCreateFailed, \n\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to create sandbox: %v\", err))\n\t\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"create\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), err)\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\t\n\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox created successfully\")\n\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxCreated, \n\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s created\", sandboxName))\n\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"create\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), nil)\n\t\n\treturn &SandboxResult{Created: true}, nil\n}\n\n// updateSandbox updates an existing sandbox resource\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) updateSandbox(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, existing *unstructured.Unstructured, sandboxName string) (*SandboxResult, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\tlog.Info(\"Updating sandbox\", \"name\", sandboxName)\n\t\n\tstartTime := time.Now()\n\t\n\t// Build desired spec\n\tdesiredSpec, err := r.buildSandboxSpec(agentRuntime)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to build sandbox spec: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Check if update is needed\n\texistingSpec, _, _ := unstructured.NestedMap(existing.Object, \"spec\")\n\tif reflect.DeepEqual(desiredSpec, existingSpec) {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox spec unchanged, skipping update\")\n\t\treturn &SandboxResult{Created: false}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Update sandbox\n\texisting.Object[\"spec\"] = desiredSpec\n\tif err := r.Update(ctx, existing); err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to update sandbox\")\n\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxUpdateFailed, \n\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to update sandbox: %v\", err))\n\t\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"update\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n\t\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), err)\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\t\n\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox updated successfully\")\n\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxUpdated, \n\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s updated\", sandboxName))\n\tRecordSandboxOperation(\"update\", agentRuntime.Namespace, sandboxName, \n\t\ttime.Since(startTime).Seconds(), nil)\n\t\n\treturn &SandboxResult{Created: false}, nil\n}\n\n// SandboxResult represents the result of sandbox reconciliation\ntype SandboxResult struct {\n\tCreated bool\n}\n```\n\n### Delete Reconciliation\n\n```go\n// reconcileDelete handles deletion of AgentRuntime resources\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcileDelete(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\tlog.Info(\"Deleting AgentRuntime\", \"namespace\", agentRuntime.Namespace, \"name\", agentRuntime.Name)\n\t\n\t// Clean up sandbox resources\n\tsandboxName := getSandboxName(agentRuntime)\n\tsandbox := &unstructured.Unstructured{}\n\tsandbox.SetGroupVersionKind(schema.GroupVersionKind{\n\t\tGroup:   \"agents.x-k8s.io\",\n\t\tVersion: \"v1alpha1\",\n\t\tKind:    \"Sandbox\",\n\t})\n\t\n\terr := r.Get(ctx, client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: agentRuntime.Namespace,\n\t\tName:      sandboxName,\n\t}, sandbox)\n\t\n\tif err == nil {\n\t\t// Delete sandbox\n\t\tif err := r.Delete(ctx, sandbox); err != nil && !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to delete sandbox\")\n\t\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeWarning, ReasonSandboxDeleteFailed, \n\t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Failed to delete sandbox: %v\", err))\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Sandbox deleted successfully\")\n\t\tr.Recorder.Event(agentRuntime, corev1.EventTypeNormal, ReasonSandboxDeleted, \n\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"Sandbox %s deleted\", sandboxName))\n\t} else if !apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to get sandbox\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Remove finalizer\n\tif HasFinalizer(agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime) {\n\t\tif err := RemoveFinalizer(ctx, r.Client, agentRuntime, FinalizerAgentRuntime); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Failed to remove finalizer\")\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t\n\tlog.Info(\"AgentRuntime deleted successfully\")\n\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n```go\n// ReconcilerError defines the reconciler error type\ntype ReconcilerError struct {\n\tCode      string\n\tMessage   string\n\tErr       error\n\tRetryable bool\n}\n\n// Error implements the error interface\nfunc (e *ReconcilerError) Error() string {\n\tif e.Err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (caused by: %v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Err)\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n}\n\n// Unwrap returns the underlying error\nfunc (e *ReconcilerError) Unwrap() error {\n\treturn e.Err\n}\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n\tErrCodeValidationFailed = \"ValidationFailed\"\n\tErrCodeSandboxCreateFailed = \"SandboxCreateFailed\"\n\tErrCodeSandboxUpdateFailed = \"SandboxUpdateFailed\"\n\tErrCodeSandboxDeleteFailed = \"SandboxDeleteFailed\"\n\tErrCodeStatusUpdateFailed = \"StatusUpdateFailed\"\n\tErrCodeFinalizerFailed = \"FinalizerFailed\"\n\tErrCodeAPIServerError = \"APIServerError\"\n)\n\n// NewReconcilerError creates a new reconciler error\nfunc NewReconcilerError(code, message string, err error, retryable bool) *ReconcilerError {\n\treturn &ReconcilerError{\n\t\tCode:      code,\n\t\tMessage:   message,\n\t\tErr:       err,\n\t\tRetryable: retryable,\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n```go\n// HandleReconcileError handles errors during reconciliation\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) HandleReconcileError(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, err error) (ctrl.Result, error) {\n\tlog := log.FromContext(ctx)\n\t\n\tif apierrors.IsConflict(err) {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Conflict error, requeuing\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tif apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Resource not found, ignoring\")\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\tif reconcilerErr, ok := err.(*ReconcilerError); ok {\n\t\tif reconcilerErr.Retryable {\n\t\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Retryable error, requeuing\")\n\t\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n\t\t\t\treconcilerErr.Code, reconcilerErr.Message)\n\t\t\treturn ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: r.RequeueAfter}, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tlog.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error\")\n\t\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n\t\t\treconcilerErr.Code, reconcilerErr.Message)\n\t\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n\t}\n\t\n\t// Unknown error\n\tlog.Error(err, \"Unknown error during reconciliation\")\n\tr.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.ConditionFalse, ConditionTypeError, \n\t\tErrCodeAPIServerError, err.Error())\n\treturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n}\n```\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n**File**: `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler/agentruntime_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage reconciler_test\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client/fake\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n\n\truntimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n\t\"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"AgentRuntimeReconciler\", func() {\n\tvar (\n\t\tctx        context.Context\n\t\treconciler *reconciler.AgentRuntimeReconciler\n\t\tfakeClient client.Client\n\t\tscheme     *runtime.Scheme\n\t)\n\n\tBeforeEach(func() {\n\t\tctx = context.Background()\n\t\tscheme = runtime.NewScheme()\n\t\tExpect(runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme)).To(Succeed())\n\t\t\n\t\tfakeClient = fake.NewClientBuilder().\n\t\t\tWithScheme(scheme).\n\t\t\tBuild(