{"type":"text","timestamp":1775846098851,"sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","part":{"id":"prt_d78acf9810011eNKTIK47OKGNu","messageID":"msg_d78ace7bf001VJXPcL5GmtkT6J","sessionID":"ses_2875606d9ffeLxTPsrdoWvyXE6","type":"text","text":"I've written a comprehensive design document for AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-007/design.md`.\n\nThe design covers:\n\n- **Architecture**: Controller-runtime based reconcilers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n- **Reconciliation Flow**: Complete event-driven reconciliation with finalizer management\n- **Data Structures**: Reconciler configs, status conditions, predicates, and metrics\n- **API Contracts**: Detailed reconcile method implementations with proper error handling\n- **Testing Strategy**: Unit tests with fake clients and integration tests with envtest\n- **Error Handling**: Retryable/non-retryable errors with proper status updates\n- **Dependencies**: controller-runtime, client-go, agent-sandbox API, and Prometheus metrics\n- **RBAC**: Required Kubernetes permissions for the reconcilers\n- **Migration Path**: 4-phase implementation and deployment plan\n- **Success Criteria**: Comprehensive checklist for validation\n\nThe design follows Kubernetes best practices and integrates seamlessly with the existing WorkloadManager HTTP service and session store.","time":{"start":1775846098849,"end":1775846098849}}}
